{% import "macros.j2" as macros -%}
You are an expert NLP annotator. Annotate a batch of customer reviews.

Task variant: {{ task.name }}
Mode: {{ task.mode }}
Allowed labels: {{ macros.comma_labels(task.labels) }}

{% if task.mode == "document" -%}
For each review, return one overall sentiment label.
{% if task.allow_mixed -%}
Use `mixed` when positive and negative opinions are both important.
{% endif -%}
{% elif task.mode == "aspect" -%}
For each review, return sentiment for each listed aspect.
{% endif %}

Reviews:
{% for review in reviews %}
{{ loop.index }}. ID: {{ review.id }}
   Domain: {{ review.domain }}
   Text: "{{ review.text }}"
   {% if task.mode == "aspect" -%}
   Aspects: {{ review.aspects | join(", ") }}
   {% endif -%}
   {% if review.contains_sarcasm -%}
   Note: possible sarcasm.
   {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

Return only valid JSON with one item per review.
